{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d7a8c5eb-287e-480e-aa36-19fadf5b9b36","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01MrumWmtWq2HRCRvL3HUcPX","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Running tests with crash dumps"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017B1NJuexpWe5ykovXSoXkm","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-6807c08add5c48f0869e164ffb2affe5 && dotnet test --blame-crash 2>&1","description":"Run dotnet test with blame-crash","initial_wait":60},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Run dotnet test with blame-crash"}],"interactionId":"965a8f76-059b-4a4a-885b-a0a71e5a2e74","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to run `dotnet test` and collect a crash dump if any test crashes the host process. \n\nFor .NET tests, crash dump collection can be configured via:\n\n1. **Environment variables** for the .NET runtime's built-in crash dump support:\n   - `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` — enables crash dumps\n   - `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` — sets the dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n   - `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` — sets the dump file path/name pattern\n   \n2. **`dotnet test` blame options** — The `--blame-crash` flag automatically captures a crash dump when the test host process crashes, with optional flags like `--blame-crash-dump-type` to specify the dump format and `--blame-crash-collect-always` to collect dumps even in non-crash scenarios. This is the most straightforward approach for `dotnet test`.","outputTokens":464,"requestId":"A040:331FF:19956AE:1CFEDEE:69FE8F3F"},"id":"e5d55984-1cbd-4bc7-97d4-6ea4a7b786a4","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:35:04.945Z","parentId":"870f26ad-0015-4f5e-9586-60dd60576326"}
